# KB Tool Usage Conventions

## Read Tools -- Choosing the Right One

| Situation | Tool | Why |
|-----------|------|-----|
| Broad question, need context | `kb_context_search` | Full retrieval cascade: entity lookup + structural expansion + FTS, returns budgeted context pack |
| Targeted lookup by type/tags | `kb_search` | FTS with filters, returns ranked snippets |
| Know a specific entity name/ID | `kb_get_entity` | Resolves by ID/alias, returns card + backlinks + neighbors + recent sessions |
| Know the exact file path | `kb_read` | Direct file read, parsed or raw |
| Want recent activity in a scope | `kb_list_recent` | Recently updated notes, optional directory filter |

Default to `kb_context_search` when unsure. It handles entity resolution and FTS in one call.

## Write Tools -- Always With User Approval

| Tool | Writes to | When to use |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| `kb_write_session_summary` | `06-sessions/` | End of a session with meaningful KB interaction |
| `kb_create_memory_candidate` | `05-agent-memory/candidates/` | Discovered a durable fact worth persisting |
| `kb_compile_raw` | `01-wiki/` | User wants to compile a raw source into a wiki article |
| `kb_update_index` | `07-indexes/` | After adding/updating wiki articles, keep indexes current |

Show the user the content before calling any write tool. Do not write silently.

## Maintenance Tools

| Tool | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `kb_lint` | User asks for health check, or proactively before major KB operations |
| `kb_reindex` | After bulk changes, or if search results seem stale |

## Typical Sequences

**Question answering:** `kb_context_search` -> synthesize answer with citations

**Deep dive on an entity:** `kb_get_entity` -> `kb_read` on linked notes -> synthesize

**Adding knowledge:** user provides content -> prepare note -> show draft -> `kb_compile_raw` or `kb_create_memory_candidate` -> `kb_update_index`

**Session wrap-up:** summarize session -> show draft -> `kb_write_session_summary`
